description.narrative:
Key development impacts of the Project include: 
???Provision of high quality retail infrastructure: Currently there is no shopping mall in Lilongwe, the capital city of Malawi. The Project will support the development of high quality retail that meets international standards. With strong international anchor tenants and a range of retailers including smaller local companies, the shopping mall will bring quality retail services closer to the community, thus minimizing costs to consumers and helping to establish a strong retail destination;
???Job Creation: The Project will create jobs both directly and indirectly during construction and operational stages; 
???Enhanced local supply linkages: The Project will increase business opportunities to local suppliers of goods services; and 
???Formalization of the retail sector: The Project will enhance the formalization of the retail sector in the country, which is currently mostly informal. This will help increase the tax revenue to the government.
